         <abstract>
            <ab>
             The <foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa qandil</foreign> is the ritual for the Unction of the Sick in the Ethiopian Church. 
               Each of its seven sections consists of the following elements:
             the lighting of a wick, a supplication, an epistle, the Trisagion, the Prayer of the Gospel with incensing and a
               <foreign xml:lang="gez">mǝsbāk</foreign>, a Gospel reading and a prayer. This record
               corresponds to the edition     <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:1967Qandil"/> 
               </bibl>.
               <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Zanetti2010Qandil"/>
               </bibl>
            </ab>
         </abstract>
